<div class="mod_newsreader block">
<div class="layout_full block">
<h3>Research resources for the 2024/25 SUBMERGED season</h3>
<p class="info"><time datetime="2024-09-03T10:36:00+02:00">03.09.2024 - 10:36</time> by Stefanie Sieber </p>
<div class="ce_text block">
<figure class="image_container float_left" style="margin-right:25px;">
<img src="assets/images/0/SU4%20Ressorucen%20Forschung%20EN-e2d346e4.png" width="450" height="450" alt="">
</figure>
<div class="text-wrapper">
<p>The research project is a central part of the <em>FIRST </em>LEGO League and will also play a crucial role in the 2024/25 SUBMERGED season. To make it easier for you to get started and develop your projects, we have put together a wide selection of helpful videos and materials for you on our <a href="en/2024-25-season/challenge-resources/research" target="_blank" rel="noopener">research resources page</a>.</p>
<p>The videos there offer valuable insights into the challenges and topics of the current season and should inspire you to develop new ideas and deepen your knowledge. Use these resources to best prepare for your research presentation and find innovative approaches for your projects.</p>
<p>We would also like to draw your attention to an exciting international offer: <a href="https://www.skypeascientist.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Skype a Scientist</a>. You can use this platform to get in direct contact with international scientists and discuss your research project. This offers you a unique opportunity to gain in-depth insights, clarify your questions and receive valuable tips from experts.</p>  </div>
</div>
</div>
<!-- indexer::stop -->
<p class="back"><a href="en/2024-25-season/season-updates" title="Back to the news overview">Back to the news overview</a></p>
<!-- indexer::continue -->
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
